==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stacte
<hw>Stac"te</hw> <pr>(st⟦acr⟧k"t⟦esl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
Gr. <grk>stakth`</grk>, strictly fem. of <grk>stakto`s</grk> oozing out
in drops, fr. <grk>sta`zein</grk> to drop.]</ety> <def>One of the sweet
spices used by the ancient Jews in the preparation of incense. It was
perhaps an oil or other form of myrrh or cinnamon, or a kind of
storax.</def> <rj><au>Ex. xxx. 34.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Staddle</ent>⟦br⟧
